{
  "stem": "19550.8",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 59.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were walking skeletons, even though that I was in [INAUDIBLE] maybe for about three months or so, so it was three months of after arriving in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "All you had to do was to look at us and you would see what condition we were in.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And again, in that particular case, you know, they were passing by, people were passing by on the road.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Our camp was in a little valley and the road was in a little elevation.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they could see the camp.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I could see what was happening.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They recognized that they must have been starving, because of the way they appeared and they looked.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And you know, a lot of people, of course, were also aware of the fact that the Germans themselves didn't have too much.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, people will probably never be able to quite recognize what hunger can do to you.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Hunger is not just a desire to eat.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Hunger is something that breaks down your, your being, your identity and your humanness.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When everything else in the world ceases to exist, the only thing that you feel and that you are aware of is that, that terrible pain, that, that urge, that, that unbelievable desire to stuff something into your mouth.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You become, you know, virtually like a single-celled animal that wants to put the food down in one end and let it come out on the other end, and nothing else exists but that one, single function.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Hunger, you can't imagine what it does to human beings.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's not, it's not just starvation or famine, it destroys your human identity.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
